    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="341" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-06-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 5,
                            1889</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 215.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                        195, of the 18th ultimo, concerning the protection of George Meimar, a
                        naturalized citizen of Turkish origin, in whose case the Ottoman Government
                        joins issue on the main question of recognition of his American citizenship
                        on the ground that he has not received an imperial iradé permitting him to
                        assume a foreign allegiance.</p>
                <p>The action of Mr. Emmet in behalf of Mr. Meimar is approved, and you are
                        instructed to make energetic remonstrance against any action on the part of
                        the Turkish Government tending in any manner to deny or abridge his just
                        rights as such American citizen.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
